AVIAN INFLUENZA (47): ITALY (LOMBARDY) POULTRY, LPAI H5N3, OIE
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 22 Jun 2020
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2020; 33(26) [edited] https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=34785


Low pathogenic avian influenza (poultry), Italy
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on 23 Jun 2020 from Dr Silvio Borrello, Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Safety and Collegial Bodies for Health Protection, [Ministry of Health], Department for Veterinary Public Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 15 Jun 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 16 Jun 2020
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 24 Apr 2020
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Low pathogenic avian influenza [LPAI] virus
Serotype: H5N3
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (LPAI_1_2020_MN): Suzzara, Mantova, Lombardia [Lombardy]
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jun 2020
Outbreak status: resolved 20 Jun 2020
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 132 / 5 / 0 / 132 / 0
Affected population: the positivity concerns an ostrich farm located in the municipality of Suzzara, in the Province of Mantova. On [20 Jun 2020] all the animals present were killed and destroyed. The animals present were 132 and the cases [5].

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 3.79 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; zoning; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; stamping out; disinfection;
vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZS) of Venice, Padua (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Birds / haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT) / 16 Jun 2020 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In April 2020, Italy detected 2 outbreaks of LPAI subtype H7N1.The affected population was 2 commercial turkey farms located in the municipality of Ormelle, Province of Treviso, Region of Veneto.

Total animals affected were:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 14 300 / 14 300 / 0 / 14 300 / 0

This event was resolved on 24 Apr 2020 and was reported to the OIE on 22 Jun 2020. See report and updated map at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=34784. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED map of Italy: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7507474,66942]
